Sam Bennett was involved in a 50-rider pile-up at the Scheldeprijs one day Classic in Belgium on Monday . 
  The 24-year-old Bora-Argon 18 rider was taken to hospital after the crash . 
  He suffered cuts to his back and shoulders in the final kilometre of the race . 
  Bradley Wiggins and Geraint Thomas were involved in the crash but avoided injury . 
  Alexander Kristoff of Katusha won the race in Belgium . 
 